This is the protocol for a review and there is no abstract. The objectives are as follows:, 1. To determine the effects (both harms and benefits) of using intravenous magnesium before, during or immediately after CABG surgery for preventing postoperative atrial fibrillation., 2. To determine the relative risk of atrial fibrillation due to intravenous magnesium compared to placebo control., 3. To determine if the effect of intravenous magnesium varies according to dose, timing and duration of magnesium administration